  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0baf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb0\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Train services started after heavy pressure from people",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Railway Station Managers' Association has stated that the general public has strongly insisted that trains be put into service to participate in the protest in the capital city of Colombo.",
        "The Railway Station Principals' Association further informed that train services to Colombo have started from Kandy, Galle, Avisawala, Anuradhapuram and Matara railway stations."
